  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="updated">Last updated: May 16, 2025</p>

  <p>The <strong>Color Blindness Helper</strong> app is developed by <strong>Tuesday Inventive</strong>.
  This policy explains how the app handles user data.</p>

  <h2>1. Data Stored on Device</h2>
  <p>The app stores the following data <strong>locally on your device only</strong>. No data is transmitted to any server:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Selected language preference</li>
    <li>Selected color blindness type</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This data is stored in Android SharedPreferences and can be deleted by clearing app data or uninstalling the app.</p>

  <h2>2. Camera Usage</h2>
  <p>The app uses your device camera for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Color ID</strong> — identifying colors in real time</li>
    <li><strong>Filter</strong> — applying daltonization correction to the live camera feed</li>
    <li><strong>Simulate</strong> — displaying a split-view comparison of original vs. simulated color vision</li>
  </ul>
  <p>All camera processing is performed <strong>entirely on your device</strong>. No camera images or video are stored, uploaded, or transmitted to any server.</p>

  <h2>3. Data Not Collected</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>The app has no user accounts and requires no registration</li>
    <li>The app does not transmit any data to Tuesday Inventive servers</li>
    <li>The app does not collect location, contacts, or any personal information</li>
    <li>Camera data is processed in real time and never saved without explicit user action</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Advertising (Google AdMob)</h2>
  <p>The app displays ads via <strong>Google AdMob</strong>. Google may collect the following to serve relevant ads:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Advertising ID (device ad identifier)</li>
    <li>Aggregated, non-personal app usage data</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Users can reset or opt out of personalized ads in Android <em>Settings → Google → Ads</em>.<br>
  For Google's privacy policy, visit:
  <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">policies.google.com/privacy</a></p>

  <h2>5. Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>CAMERA</strong> — Required for Color ID, Filter, and Simulate screens</li>
    <li><strong>READ_MEDIA_IMAGES / READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE</strong> — Required to select images from gallery in Simulate screen</li>
    <li><strong>INTERNET</strong> — Required to load AdMob ads</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The app does not request access to microphone, location, contacts, or other personal data.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
  <p>All preference data remains on your device. Camera frames are processed in memory and immediately discarded. Tuesday Inventive has no access to any user data.</p>

  <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>This app does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 13.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>If this policy is updated, the changes will be reflected on this page with a revised date.</p>

  <h2>9. Contact</h2>
  <p>For questions about this policy, contact:<br>
  <a href="mailto:tuesday.inventive@gmail.com">tuesday.inventive@gmail.com</a></p>

